fpdf>=1.7.2  # ships no wheel (sdist only) - exempted from --only-binary :all: below.
# The actively-maintained fpdf2 fork is API-compatible on paper, but its
# multi_cell() is measurably stricter about available horizontal space and
# raises FPDFException on input this project's report_generator.py already
# renders fine under classic fpdf - confirmed by actually generating a report
# with fpdf2 installed, not just reading the changelog. Migrating is a real,
# separate task (review every cell()/multi_cell() call, re-verify every
# report section), not a side effect of a CI hardening pass.

